Sentencas: A novel Sr-based perovskite electrolyte, SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1Gd0.05O3-delta, was successfully synthesized and characterized in comparison with SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1Sm0.05O3-delta for possible use in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: High conductivity and high density SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1A0.05O3-δ (A = Gd, Sm) proton-conducting electrolytes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Indexing and subsequent Rietveld refinement confirm that both materials crystallize in the orthorhombic symmetry with Pbnm space group.
Titulo: High conductivity and high density SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1A0.05O3-δ (A = Gd, Sm) proton-conducting electrolytes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy images show the highly dense structure with the relative densities of 96% and 97% for Gd and Sm-doped sample, respectively.
Titulo: High conductivity and high density SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1A0.05O3-δ (A = Gd, Sm) proton-conducting electrolytes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance measurements in wet 5% hydrogen at 700 degrees C shows that the conductivity of SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1Gd0.05O3-delta and SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1Sm0.05O3-delta were 5.701 x10(-3) S cm(-1) and 5.257 x 10(-3) S cm(-1), respectively.
Titulo: High conductivity and high density SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1A0.05O3-δ (A = Gd, Sm) proton-conducting electrolytes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The ionic conductivities of both samples increase in the wet hydrogen compared with that of dry hydrogen atmosphere.
Titulo: High conductivity and high density SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1A0.05O3-δ (A = Gd, Sm) proton-conducting electrolytes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: This indicates the enhancement of protonic conduction mechanism from introducing water in electrochemical impedance measurement.
Titulo: High conductivity and high density SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1A0.05O3-δ (A = Gd, Sm) proton-conducting electrolytes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The proton conduction takes place at a lower temperature than conventional solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) which makes SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1(Gd/Sm)(0.05)O3-delta good electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: High conductivity and high density SrCe0.5Zr0.35Y0.1A0.05O3-δ (A = Gd, Sm) proton-conducting electrolytes for IT-SOFCs
